        <h1>resteasy-json-xml</h1>

        <p>This project aims to explain how to use <strong>RESTeasy 1.2.1.GA</strong> with <strong>JBoss EAP 5.1.2</strong> when you deal with <strong>@Form</strong> and <strong>@FormParam</strong>.</p>

        <p>Also you will find how to use URL-based content negotation to retrieve data in the format you like.</p>

        <p>Soon I'll code the same project using <strong>RESTeasy 2</strong>.</p>

        <h2>What you need is:</h2>

        <ul>
            <li>Maven 2+</li>
            <li>JDK 5+</li>
            <li>JBoss EAP 5.1.2 or JBoss AS 6</li>
            <li>The IDE you like, preferably a good one. Any <strong>IDEA</strong> out there? ;-)</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Why am I sharing this?</h2>

        <p>I'm sure I'll need that sooner or later!</p>
